                    <div class="titleblock">installation</div>
                    <p>Installing Peek into Github in your NetBeans IDE is easy.</p>
					<p>You'll need:
						<ul>
							<li>NetBeans IDE 7.0 or later</li>
							<li>A working Internet connection (for fetching data from github.com)</li>							
						</ul>
					</p>
					<p>Simply follow these steps to get Peek into Github up and running in your NetBeans IDE:
                    	<ol>
                    		<li>Download Peek into Github. See the <a href='download.html'>download</a> page.</li>
                    		<li>Extract the zipball at a convenient location.</li>
							<li>You'll notice that you have extracted 3 <code>.nbm</code> files among others.</li>
							<li>Start your NetBeans IDE.</li>
							<li>On the menu bar, click the <strong>Tools</strong> &raquo; <strong>Plugins</strong> menu item.</li>
							<li>In the <strong>Plugins</strong> window, click the <strong>Downloads</strong> tab.</li>
							<li>In the <strong>Downloads</strong> tab, click the <strong>Add plugins...</strong> button.</li>
							<li>In the <strong>Add Plugins</strong> window, browse to the location where you extracted the zipball.</li>
							<li>Select the three <code>.nbm</code> files:
								<ul>
									<li><code>risbee-pig-core.nbm</code></li>
									<li><code>risbee-pig-lib-githubjavasdk.nbm</code></li>
									<li><code>risbee-pig-lib-gson.nbm</code></li>								
								</ul>
							</li>
							<li>Click the <strong>Open</strong> button.</li>
							<li>Click the <strong>Install</strong> button.</li>
							<li>Follow the on-screen wizard's instructions and complete the installation.</li>
						</ol>
					</p>
                    <div class="titleblock">startubg</div>
                    <p>Once installed, Peek into Github can be launched by clicking the <strong>Window</strong> &raquo; <strong>Pig</strong> menu item. You should now see the Peek into Github panel on your right.</p>
					<div class="titleblock">viewing all your repositories</div>
                    <p></p>
					<div class="titleblock">viewing individual repository details</div>
                    <p></p>
					<div class="titleblock">refreshing</div>
                    <p></p>
					<div class="titleblock">other options</div>
                    <p></p>
                </div>
